  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong>, then unwrap the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add the <strong>pastry</strong> to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Cut the string<strong> </strong>from the <strong>turkey joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and add it to one side of the puff pastry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636447035718-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636447035718-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636447035718-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636447035718-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636447035718-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>turkey joint</strong> up in the pastry (like a sausage roll!) and then pinch the sides together to seal it</p><p>Score the top of the <strong>pastry</strong> with a fork and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>turkey wellington</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Repeat this process!</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven for 35-40 min or until the pastry is golden and the turkey is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636447040479-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636447040479-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636447040479-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636447040479-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1636447040479-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the wellington is in the oven, boil a full kettle</p><p>Remove the tough stalks from the <strong>cavolo nero</strong> and chop finely</p><p>Tip: Bunch up the leaves and roll them like a cigar before slicing!</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636447044137-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636447044137-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636447044137-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636447044137-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1636447044137-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636447047141-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636447047141-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636447047141-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636447047141-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1636447047141-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped cavolo nero </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until wilted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636447051334-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636447051334-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636447051334-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636447051334-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1636447051334-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the cavolo nero is cooking, dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the cavolo nero is done, transfer it to a plate and cover tightly with <strong>tin-foil</strong> to keep warm until serving – this is your <strong>garlic cavolo nero</strong></p><p>Wipe the pan clean and return it to a medium-high heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1636447054706-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1636447054706-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1636447054706-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1636447054706-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1636447054706-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once melted, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and give it a good mix up until a sandy-like paste has formed – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Stir in the <strong>beef stock </strong>and add the<strong> wholegrain mustard</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>mustardy gravy</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1636447059059-x200.jpg",
